  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Through FY2026 to date, Department of Defense contract obligations total $239B across 2,049,180 awards, with an average award size of $116K. Obligations are down 51.5% year over year; current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date). Annual obligations peaked in FY25 at $492B and declined to $239B in FY26. Earlier fiscal years show $387B in FY21, $414B in FY22, $457B in FY23, and $446B in FY24. Top procurement categories for FY2026 to date include Aircraft Manufacturing at $31.1B, Engineering Services at $22.8B, and Guided Missile and Space Vehicle Manufacturing at $21.6B. Defense also obligated funds for Research and Development at $16.2B and medical-related carriers at $11.8B. The largest single vendors in FY2026 to date include LOCKHEED MARTIN CORPORATION with awards of $10B and $8.8B, ELECTRIC BOAT CORPORATION at $8.3B, THE BOEING COMPANY at $5.8B and $4.3B, and RAYTHEON COMPANY at $4.8B. These figures reflect obligations recorded through the fiscal year to date.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "How has Defense contract spending changed from recent fiscal years?",
        "body": "Obligations fell 51.5% year over year, with FY26 at $239B compared with FY25 at $492B. Earlier fiscal years show $387B in FY21, $414B in FY22, $457B in FY23, and $446B in FY24. The FY26 total is a partial, fiscal year to date figure."
      },
      {
        "heading": "What are the largest procurement categories and top vendors in FY2026 to date?",
        "body": "The top NAICS categories include Aircraft Manufacturing at $31.1B, Engineering Services at $22.8B, and Guided Missile and Space Vehicle Manufacturing at $21.6B, with Research and Development at $16.2B and Direct Health and Medical Insurance Carriers at $11.8B. Top vendors include LOCKHEED MARTIN CORPORATION at $10B and $8.8B, ELECTRIC BOAT CORPORATION at $8.3B, THE BOEING COMPANY at $5.8B and $4.3B, and RAYTHEON COMPANY at $4.8B."
      }
